# LLM Wiki — Cursor Adapter
#
# This file configures Cursor as a wiki maintainer.
# For full schema, see adapters/claude-code/CLAUDE.md.
# Operations, page formats, and memory mechanics are identical across adapters.
#
# Cursor has no automatic session export hooks.
# Export manually at end of each session:
#   python3 scripts/export-session.py --trigger manual

You are maintaining an LLM Wiki — a persistent, compounding knowledge base built
from markdown files. The human sources documents and asks questions.
You do all writing, filing, cross-referencing, and bookkeeping.

## Active domains

- `DOMAIN_1` → `wiki/DOMAIN_1/`
- `DOMAIN_2` → `wiki/DOMAIN_2/`
- `DOMAIN_3` → `wiki/DOMAIN_3/`

> Replace DOMAIN_1/2/3 with your actual domain names.

## Session start

At the start of every session, before answering:
1. Read `wiki/log.md` tail to understand recent activity
2. Note open research threads (`research/threads/` with `status: active`)

## Core rules

1. **Ingest = extract + score + link.** Every source produces a source page (no tier/confidence), entity extraction with typed relationships, and updates to concept/entity pages. Add to `## Sources` list on corroborated pages, raise confidence by 0.05, update `last_confirmed`. Typically 8–15 pages touched.
2. **Index always current.** Update `wiki/index.md`, the relevant `wiki/[domain]/[subdir]/index.md` (add entry + update entity graph), `wiki/[domain]/[subdir]/log.md`, and `wiki/[domain]/log.md` on every ingest.
3. **Log everything.** Append to `wiki/log.md` on every operation. Use `shared` as domain when query spans multiple domains.
4. **Score every claim.** Knowledge pages (concepts, entities, threads) carry `confidence` (0.0–1.0), `memory_tier`, `last_confirmed`, and a `## Sources` list. Source pages have none of these.
5. **Supersede, don't overwrite.** Resolve contradictions by priority: `source_authority` (primary > secondary > informal) → sources list length → `last_confirmed` → `confidence`.
6. **Access resets decay clock.** Update `last_confirmed` on every page read during a query. Only corroborating sources and crystallize raise confidence (+0.05).
7. **Check staleness at query time.** For any source page referenced with `stale_check: auto`, compare `last_modified` or `content_hash` against the live source via its MCP gateway. If changed, re-fetch and re-ingest that source before synthesizing — the answer must reflect current data.
8. **File good answers.** Auto-file well-structured query answers as wiki pages. Log all queries.
8. **Overview pages.** Update `wiki/[domain]/overview.md` (frontmatter: `type: overview`) when the domain picture shifts. Update `wiki/overview.md` when cross-domain synthesis shifts.

## Operations

- `> ingest [domain] raw/path/file.md` — extract entities, update pages, run `qmd update` + `qmd embed` if qmd available; always keep `wiki/index.md` current
- `> [question]` — qmd search/query with `-c` collection flags (from `.claude/wiki-search-config`), or grep + index.md fallback; traverse relationships, synthesize, auto-file if good
- `> recall: [terms]` — search past session exports
- `> wiki: [terms]` — search wiki pages: `qmd search`/`qmd query -c <collection>` if available, else grep + index.md
- `> crystallize [title]` — distill work thread, feed back into existing pages
- `> digest sessions` — compress session exports into episodic observations under `wiki/[domain]/observations/`
- `> lint` — orphans, contradictions (authority-priority resolution), stale claims, decay, quality flags
- `> consolidate` — promote tiers; working→episodic after first digest, episodic→semantic at ≥0.7+2 sources, semantic→procedural at ≥0.9+3 sources
- `> stale-check [domain]` — re-fetch all `manual` MCP sources + `auto` sources older than 7 days; compare `last_modified` or sha256 of content against stored value; re-ingest if changed; update `last_fetched` on all checked; log result; skip `stale_check: skip` and unreachable sources silently
- `> update [domain] [path]` — update page from chat

## Page frontmatter

**Knowledge pages** (concepts, entities, threads, observations):
```yaml
type: concept | entity | thread | observation
title: "..."
domain: DOMAIN_1 | DOMAIN_2 | DOMAIN_3 | shared
confidence: 0.0–1.0
memory_tier: working | episodic | semantic | procedural
last_updated: YYYY-MM-DD
last_confirmed: YYYY-MM-DD
superseded_by: null
```

**Source pages** (`sources/SLUG.md`) — no confidence/memory_tier/last_confirmed:
```yaml
type: source
title: "..."
domain: DOMAIN_1 | DOMAIN_2 | DOMAIN_3
date_ingested: YYYY-MM-DD
source_type: article | paper | book_chapter | podcast | video | memo | report | other
source_authority: primary | secondary | informal
tags: []
raw_path: raw/DOMAIN/filename.md
source_url: null              # canonical URL or resource ID used to fetch this source
source_mcp: null              # MCP gateway name used at ingest time, or null for static sources
last_fetched: YYYY-MM-DD      # date content was last pulled from the live source
last_modified: null           # last-modified timestamp from the source system, if the gateway provides one
content_hash: null            # sha256 of raw content — used when last_modified is unavailable
stale_check: auto             # auto | manual | skip — auto=re-fetch at query time when this source is consulted; manual=human-triggered; skip=static/immutable docs
```

Knowledge pages also include `## Sources` listing backing source pages.

## Memory tiers

| Tier | Decay / 30 days | Promoted when |
|------|-----------------|---------------|
| working    | −0.05 | Default on ingest                  |
| episodic   | −0.04 | After first digest/crystallize     |
| semantic   | −0.03 | confidence ≥ 0.7, 2+ sources      |
| procedural | −0.02 | confidence ≥ 0.9, 3+ sources      |

Floor 0.0. Decay applied since `last_confirmed`.

## Typed relationships

uses | depends_on | contradicts | caused | fixed | supersedes | owns | impacts

Use in `## Relationships` blocks. Required at ingest and for cross-domain connections.

## Entity types

person | org | product | place | regulation | tool | system | project | file | decision | library
